Join our innovative team as a Data Scientist (Generative AI) – Senior Manager to spearhead projects using Azure Open AI, AWS and Local models to create cutting-edge generative AI applications. This role is ideal for those with foundational skills in AI and software development, and who are eager to grow their expertise in generative AI technologies.




Responsibilities

Design and implement AI models using Azure Open AI services preferably with Python to solve business problems;
Prompt engineering;
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate AI capabilities into broader tech infrastructures;
Close relation to Business Process Subject Matter Experts for building the solution and better prompting;
Maintain and improve the performance of existing AI systems;
Conduct A/B testing and performance tuning to enhance model efficacy and efficiency.
Participate in code reviews and adhere to software development best practices;
Assist in defining project scopes and timelines.




Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in computer science, engineering, AI, or a related field;
5 years of Data Science or related Software Development experience with exposure to AI/ML-based project implementations and 1-3 years of Gen AI (LLM) experience;
Proficiency in Python and another major programming language, data structures, data post processing in padas data frames and work with JSON structures;
Understanding of machine learning algorithms;
Experience with Microsoft Azure and specifically Azure Open AI services at least in terms of Code Integrations with Azure;
Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work in a team environment.




Nice to have:

Experience in developing and deploying generative AI models;
Practical knowledge of REST APIs and web services;
Familiarity with AI ethics and responsible AI use;
Project portfolio with examples of AI solutions, particularly in generative AI is a plus.




What can we offer:

Attractive salary package;
Great career development opportunities;
Free access to our award-winning learning platform;
Ongoing training in Azure Open AI and other relevant AI technologies;
Regular participation in workshops and webinars focused on the latest AI advancements;
Access to a library of resources and courses for continuous learning in AI and machine learning;
Comprehensive benefits package including life and medical insurance, additional vacation days, partner discounts, and more country-specific perks;
Referral program, empowering employees to recommend qualified candidates and earn rewards for successful hires.
